  "text": "One can try to use debiasing methods to reduce the effects of cognitive biases in preference elicitation and in estimation tasks involving expert judgment. Ideas for debiasing have been suggested in the decision analysis literature. These ideas relate to problem framing, design of elicitation questions, better training, and calibration of judgments (see, e.g. [CITATION_1] ). Lahtinen and Hämäläi-nen [CITATION_2] propose that besides reducing biases in single preference elicitation tasks one can also attempt to design the elicitation procedure so that the effects of biases cancel each other out. So far, research on the effectiveness of debiasing methods remains very limited.",
